oai_dc:dc.dc:title: DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION OF PLEASURE CRAFT HARBOUR - CLUB MYKONOS LANGEBAAN
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bosman, D.E.
Retief, G. de F.
Kapp, J.F.
Kloos, M.
Ridge, A.B.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: harbor
pleasure craft harbor
case study
Clum Mykonos Langebaan
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A description of the pre-design investigation, design and construction of a pleasure craft harbour is given. The influence of the breakwaters on the sedimentation pattern in the direct vicinity of the harbour during construction and after completion of the harbour is described. Adaption of the design of some of the harbour components due to unforeseen circumstances revealed during the construction period is also discussed.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 22 (1990): Proceedings of 22nd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Delft, The Netherlands, 1990.
